stats-0.0.1 changelog (from unreleased version)
	-separate structures for table and stats calculation variables
	-functions return error codes or NULL to indicate errors
	-all function calls in main() handle errors
	-headers have guards against being included multiple times
	-rewrote program from scratch
	-no menu: table is written in a separate file and read in (argc/argv)
	-rename variables 
	-better error checking in functions (functions are self contained & don't rely on 
		checks in other functions). functions check their own parameters. 
	-clearer error messages
	-added -v/--version command line option
	-table and stats calculations printed in engineering format
	-added minimum and maximum functions for x & y arrays
	-added DEBUG macro in debug.h to turn on debug mode (DEBUG 0 debug mode is off, DEBUG 1 debig mode is on
	-other miscellaneous changes I forgot about 
